# Reading List Extension Specification

## Overview

A quick and easy way to save web pages for later reading. Add pages with a single command and organize them with custom tags.

## Features

### Page Management

- Command: Add Page
- Arguments: URL
- Functionality:
  - Saves the page with metadata (title, description, image, favicon)
  - Automatically detects if the page already exists
  - Updates existing pages if URL matches

### Tag Management

- Command: Create Tag
- Arguments: None
- Functionality:
  - Creates new tags with custom names and colors
  - Tag name validation:
    - Maximum 10 characters
    - Only alphanumeric characters and hyphens allowed
    - Unique names required

### Page Listing

- Command: List Pages
- Arguments: None
- Functionality:
  - Displays saved pages with:
    - Title
    - URL
    - Description
    - Image preview
    - Favicon
    - Tags
    - Creation/Update timestamps
    - Read status

### Page Actions

- Open in browser (marks as read)
- Toggle read status
- Delete page
- Add/remove tags

## Data Structure

### Page

```ts
interface Page {
  url: string;         // Unique URL
  title: string;       // Page title
  description: string; // Page description
  imageUrl: string;    // Preview image URL
  faviconUrl: string;  // Favicon URL
  tagIds: string[];    // Associated tag IDs
  createdAt: string;   // ISO timestamp
  updatedAt: string;   // ISO timestamp
  isRead: boolean;     // Read status
}
```

### Tag

```ts
interface Tag {
  id: string;    // Unique ID
  name: string;  // Tag name
  color: string; // Tag color
}
```

## Technical Requirements

- Data Persistence: Raycast Storage API
- Metadata Extraction: OGP and HTML meta tags
- Error Handling:
  - Invalid URLs
  - Failed page fetches
  - Storage operation failures
  - Tag validation errors

## UI/UX
- Modern, clean interface
- Color-coded tags for easy identification
- Quick actions for common operations
- Toast notifications for feedback
- Form validation with clear error messages
